</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>

<h2>The Traffic Factor</h2>

<p>Do not underestimate Melaka's traffic. Getting from Klebang to Jonker on a Saturday night can take 45 minutes. Guests staying in Klebang usually skip Jonker and stick to the <strong>Klebang Coconut Shake</strong> area or drive to <strong>Porta de Santiago</strong> early morning.</p>

<p><strong>iHousing Strategy:</strong> For Klebang properties, we market "Staycation" packages (board games, BBQ pits, beach gear) because guests spend more time <em>inside</em> the unit. For Jonker properties, we focus on <strong>walking distance</strong> convenience.</p>

<div class="bg-gray-100 p-6 rounded-lg my-8">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4">
        <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold">Which location is best for Airbnb investment in Melaka?</h3>
            <p>Jonker is better for steady occupancy and rental yield, while Klebang is better for large family groups and capital appreciation due to newer developments and coastal appeal.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold">What is the occupancy rate for Airbnb in Melaka?</h3>
            <p>On average, heritage zones (Jonker) see 85%+ occupancy on weekends and 50-60% on weekdays. Coastal areas like Klebang see 90% on weekends but lower weekday rates around 30%.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
